On **.NET 10**, you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property is the .NET 9-and-earlier shim. Instead, add a `"test"` section to `global.json`:

```json
{
  "sdk": { "version": "10.0.100" },
  "test": { "runner": "Microsoft.Testing.Platform" }
}
```

This enables native MTP mode in `dotnet test` — arguments like `--report-trx` are passed directly (no `--` separator needed).

